4.    Write a program that accepts  a string from the user and display the string after replacing the vowel character with @
 
PROGRAM:
 
str=input("Enter the string:")
char=input("Enter a character:")
newstr=""
for i in range(len(str)):
    if str[i]=="a" or str[i]=="e" or str[i]=="i" or str[i]=="o" or str[i]=="u":
        newstr=newstr+char
    else:
        newstr=newstr+str[i]
print("\n original string:",str)
print("new string:",newstr)
 
OUTPUT:
 
Enter the string:college
Enter a character:@
 
 original string: college
new string: c@ll@g@

